#Reliance   Reliance #Q1FY24 Performance  Oil 2 Chemical segment: •)PAT declining 6% year-on-year due to a sharp decline in oil to chemicals revenues because of 31% fall in crude oil prices.  •)EBITDA grew by 5% Year-on-Year due to higher production in the oil & gas segment led.  •)Rise in finance costs due to higher interest rates and loan balances has led to decline in PAT( net profit ).  •)Diversified revenue streams with strong performances by retail and telecom helped RIL to manage the O2C segment impact on its Q1-FY24 performance.  •)O2C business revenue dipped 17.7% over Q1-FY23, for the second consecutive quarter.  Telecom Segment: •)The company( jio-Telecom segment ) registered a significant improvement led by the addition of 29 million subscribers, higher data consumption due to 5G adoption, and a 3% improvement in ARPU.  Retail Segment: •)Revenues grew by 20% driven by a rapid expansion in the retail space area, while revenue per square feet continued to be moderate.  •)The Grocery business led the growth by 59% YoY growth in the Smart and the Smart Bazaars.  •)The Fashion and lifestyle business grew 15% YoY, driven by a pick-up in store traffic as well as average bill value.   •)The digital and new commerce business( jio Mart & Ajio ) continued to grow contributing 18% of the revenues.  Conclusion: Performance of legacy businesses ( O2C Segment )was Slow down in Q1 FY24 and the new-age businesses, such as retail, media, digital, and renewables, would continue to drive the Business Growth.

#JioFinancialServices : All you need to know about the spin-off  📅 Record date: The record date for the spin-off is July 20. This means that any shareholder who holds shares in #Reliance Industries on this date will be eligible to receive shares in Jio Financial Services.  ⚖️ Ratio: The ratio of shares is 1:1, meaning that for every share of Reliance Industries held, shareholders will receive one share of Jio Financial Services.  📢 Special session: The #NSE will hold a special pre-open session on July 20 to determine the price discovery of the two new entities. The price of Jio Financial Services will be set at a discount to the price of Reliance Industries.  📈 #Nifty: Jio Financial Services will be included in the #Nifty50 as its 51st stock. It will stay there at a constant price until it is listed, and then it will be removed from the Nifty.  💰 Market valuation: The market is valuing Jio Financial Services at Rs 160-200 per share, based on its treasury stock. However, the company has not yet released any growth targets or projections, so the market valuation is still uncertain.
